The paper combines insights from Mining Software Repositories (MSR) and Search-based Software Engineering (SBSE), which are both subfields of software engineering. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper also mentions the use of meta-heuristic algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data mining techniques (cs.IR) and the analysis of large datasets (cs.DB).
